WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:02.210
<i>Previously on Boston Legal...</i>

00:02.250 --> 00:03.850
–Who is this guy?
–Melvin Palmer.

00:03.890 --> 00:05.670
State of Utah vs Denny Crane.

00:05.710 --> 00:07.650
I'll represent the hoot brothers.

00:07.689 --> 00:10.890
For once in your life,
let me do the talking.

00:10.900 --> 00:12.370
Denny!

00:12.390 --> 00:15.070
We were just—
–Do you love him?

00:15.080 --> 00:16.740
I think I do.

00:16.770 --> 00:20.670
This man makes partner, or I walk and
take my name off the door with me.

00:20.710 --> 00:22.200
–Edwin Poole.
–Denny Crane.

00:22.240 --> 00:23.730
–Name on the door.
–Mine, too.

00:23.770 --> 00:25.580
–Crane…
–Poole and…

00:25.590 --> 00:27.470
Schmidt.

00:29.000 --> 00:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:48.550 --> 00:50.590
Drop the bag, and I'll let you live!

00:50.630 --> 00:53.570
Do it, bitch. Don't make me cap you.

00:53.580 --> 00:57.350
Son, of all the places you could stick
me —you may have already stuck me—

00:57.390 --> 00:58.830
I'd probably be the last to know.

00:58.870 --> 01:00.650
–Drop the bag.
–Turnip!

01:00.660 --> 01:03.070
For God's sake,
what the hell are you…

01:03.110 --> 01:04.810
–Shirley?
–Edwin?

01:04.819 --> 01:06.340
Put that down.
What is wrong with you?

01:06.380 --> 01:07.630
I am so sorry, Shirley.

01:07.670 --> 01:10.280
Of all the people to
mug… I'll deal with him.

01:10.320 --> 01:14.412
This woman is a dear friend of
mine, not to mention a partner.

01:14.470 --> 01:17.420
Oh, I'm sorry, ma'am.

01:18.150 --> 01:21.530
Edwin, who is this… adorable child?

01:21.540 --> 01:24.430
He's my foster—give me
that! He's my foster son.

01:24.470 --> 01:26.940
I am so sorry, Shirley.
God, what is wrong with you?

01:26.980 --> 01:28.080
You adopted a son?

01:28.120 --> 01:30.120
Yeah, it was either that
or take up fly-fishing.

01:30.160 --> 01:32.580
Shame, Turnip. Shame.

01:32.590 --> 01:34.540
Look how full your cart is.

01:34.550 --> 01:36.490
No wonder your bottom is so—
–Turnip.

01:36.530 --> 01:39.350
–Full and plump.
–He gets cuter by the second.

01:39.390 --> 01:42.810
Isn't it the truth? Well, that's enough
now. Turnip Graves, Shirley Schmidt.

01:42.850 --> 01:44.570
Very nice to meet you, ma'am.

01:44.610 --> 01:46.200
A true pleasure, sir.

01:46.210 --> 01:47.620
Well, it's—it's nice
to see you again.

01:47.660 --> 01:51.240
You look great, and, uh, I'll
deal with him. Come here, you.

01:51.280 --> 01:52.760
Why would you do that and
embarrass me like that?

01:52.800 --> 01:54.930
How was I supposed to
know you'd know the lady?

01:54.970 --> 01:56.850
I know you're not supposed
to walk around parking lots

01:56.890 --> 01:59.860
sticking people in the
buttocks with a knife.

